# IR Remote → Python

## Overview

Reads IR remote button presses with Arduino and sends the HEX codes to Python. Arduino also identifies which button was pressed.

## What I Learned

* Using the IRremote library.
* Reading IR signals and sending data over Serial.
* Mapping HEX codes to button names.

## Problems Faced

* Old IRremote code didn't work.
* Unsure about repeat (`0`) codes.

## Solution

* Updated to the latest IRremote API.
* Learned that `0` is the repeat signal when a button is held.

## My Work

* Built the Python Serial reader.
* Connected and tested the IR receiver.
* Mapped buttons using constants and added button recognition.

## AI Assistance

* ChatGPT: Updated old IRremote code, explained repeat codes, and reviewed the project.
* GitHub Copilot: Suggested small code improvements while coding.
